  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1620676/" class="title-link">從次文化到虛擬文化</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1620676"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/aco_books/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2676624-4.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/aco_books/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">aco_books</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2009-01-15"
      class="main-meta">2009-01-15 20:38:26</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1620676_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  電腦、互聯網是現代人賴以溝通的工具。但在60年代的越戰及冷戰時期，電腦卻是公眾忌諱之物，因為這種發明當時普遍認為只能夠用於強化工業、軍事、器械等發展。直至90年代互聯網面世，電腦卻締造了一個虛擬的烏托邦，那是一個協作互利與分享的世界，這些正是60年代嬉皮士所追求...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 1没用</span>
                        <span class="publisher left">
                            University Of Chicago Press2006版</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
